item.description:
Multi Query Attention Multi Query Attention (MQA) using the same $K$ and $V$ matrices for each head in our multi head self attention mechanism. For a given head, $h$, $1 \leq h \leq H$, the attention mechanism is calculated as
\begin{equation} h_i = \text{attention}(M\cdot W_h^Q, M \cdot W^K,M \cdot W^V). \end{equation}
For each of our $H$ heads, the only difference in the weight matrices is in $W_h^Q$. Each of these $W_h$ has dimension $(n \times d_q)$.
